</table>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Connecting to this market allows for the following automatic processes to take place:</p>
</div>
<div class="ulist">
<ul>
<li>
<p>Hourly order import</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Stock synchronisation every 20 minutes</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Hourly listing synchronisation</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Automatically end listings when no stock is available (every 15 minutes)</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Automatically restart listings when new stock is available (every 15 minutes)</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Automatically create a new customer data record during the order import. This is assuming no customer data record was already saved in the database</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock tip">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-tip" title="Tip"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Automatic order import</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Orders from Hood will be imported into your plentymarkets system every hour and will be available in the <a href="/en/order-processing/orders"><strong>Orders</strong></a> menu. You can recognise Hood orders by the information displayed in the <strong>Referrer</strong> column. For lack of space, only the ID 125 is displayed. Point your cursor over an ID to view the referrer.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="400">2.1. Setting up shipping profiles</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Proceed as follows to set up shipping profiles for Hood.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Setting up shipping profiles:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>System » Markets » Hood</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Scroll down to the <strong>Shipping profiles</strong> section and click on the <strong>New</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter a <strong>name</strong> for the shipping profile.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select a <strong>region</strong> from the drop-down menu.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select a <strong>shipping method</strong> from the drop-down menu.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter the <strong>shipping costs</strong>.<br>
→ Enter any additional shipping methods and shipping costs for this region.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.<br>
→ The shipping profile will be displayed in the <strong>Overview</strong> tab. It can be edited or deleted there.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Create additional shipping profiles the same way. The shipping profiles are then available in the <strong>Base</strong> tab of a <a href="/en/omni-channel/multi-channel/hood#290"><strong>listing</strong></a>.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="450">2.2. Linking shipping profiles</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Go to the menu <strong>System » Markets » Hood » Shipping profile links</strong> to links shipping methods with a shipping profile. Settings carried out in this menu will be taken into consideration during the order import. If you do not link the shipping method the shipping profile calculation will be carried out automatically. Proceed as described below in order to link shipping methods to a shipping profile.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Linking shipping profiles:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>System » Markets » Hood » Shipping profile links</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select a <strong>Shipping profile</strong> for the desired shipping method from the drop-down menu.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="500">2.3. Setting up payment methods</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Set up the payment methods that you want to use for this market. This is done within your account on Hood. Choose between different options such as bank transfer (cash in advance), purchase on invoice or PayPal. The payment methods are then available in the listing.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="600">2.4. Automatically posting feedback</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Enter your feedback texts first. Then set up an <a href="/en/basics/automation/event-procedures"><strong>event procedure</strong></a> to automatically send your feedback texts to your buyers. All buyers who gave you feedback will automatically receive a random feedback text in return.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Entering feedback texts:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>System » Markets » Hood</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter feedback texts in the <strong>Automatic feedback</strong> section.<br>
→ These texts will be chosen randomly.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
