<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="4900">11.3. Editing active listings with batch processing</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Batch processing includes the same options as the group function. However, the batch processing function edits previously filtered listings. The filters used for narrowing down listings are the same as described for search filters in tables 18 and 20. The procedures are the same as described for group functions in table 21.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Editing active listings with batch processing:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Listings » Batch processing » Active listings</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select the filters. Pay attention to the information given in tables 18 to 20.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Carry out the settings as desired. Pay attention to the information given in table 21.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Execute</strong> to carry out the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
